FIRST GO INTO 
/home/pi/RPi_Cam_Web_Interface

left click and run the file 

	stop.sh

(execute in terminal)
this turns off the webcam application to free up the camera for opencv

now we open up the virtual machine that opencv is installed on
(copy and paste what is after the $)

	pi@raspberrypi:~ $ source ~/.profile
	pi@raspberrypi:~ $ workon cv

then run (sudo = super user do)

	(cv) pi@raspberrypi:~ $ sudo python picameraTest.py

to test the camera if you would like
it maybe upside down but you can change this by opening up the file
to quit this specific python program click on the window displaying the
video and click q


to view the code inside this python file 
	
	(cv) pi@raspberrypi:~ $ sudo nano picameraTest.py

nano is a terminal text editor and it allows you to modify 
code files such as c files or python file basically any only via the terminal
hit ctrl + x to get out of nano. it will ask to save.

run this code to run a color detection piece of code
it should track highlighter green.

	(cv) pi@raspberrypi:~ $ sudo python piOpenCVColor.py 

to modify the code go into 

	(cv) pi@raspberrypi:~ $ sudo nano piOpenCVColor.py 
